# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 5 — THREE-TIER DATA ARCHITECTURE
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

This is the foundational architectural concept. Understand it completely
before writing any code. All data flows through these three tiers.

## Tier 1 — Institution (SaaS Tenant)
  The billing unit. One subscription contract per institution.
  Super Admin (UniCore staff) manages these.
  Example: "University of Lagos" is one Institution.

## Tier 2 — InstitutionEntity (Operational Sub-Unit)
  An institution can create multiple entities to model how it actually
  operates: campuses, schools, affiliated colleges, extramural centres, etc.
  Each entity has its own governance, branding, admin staff, and OrgUnit tree.
  Institution Admin (VC, Registrar) manages these.

  Entity Types:
    MAIN_CAMPUS           Primary institution body
    SCHOOL                e.g. School of Medicine (semi-autonomous)
    EXTRAMURAL            Continuing/evening education division
    DISTANCE_LEARNING     Online/remote learning division
    SATELLITE_CAMPUS      Branch campus in another city or region
    PROFESSIONAL_SCHOOL   Law School, Business School, etc.
    SUMMER_SCHOOL         Seasonal programme
    RESEARCH_INSTITUTE    e.g. West African Research Centre
    CONSTITUENT_COLLEGE   Tightly coupled affiliated college
    AFFILIATE             Loosely coupled external partner (API only)

  Coupling Strength:
    INTERNAL   Full integration — shares staff pool, courses, fee structures
    PARTIAL    Partial — own staff, shares some services with parent
    EXTERNAL   API-level only — student verification and transcript check only

  Billing Classification:
    BILLED_TO_PARENT      Students counted in parent institution's bill
    BILLED_INDEPENDENTLY  Entity has its own subscription and invoice
    EXEMPT                Not billed (e.g. research institutes)

## Tier 3 — OrgUnit (Internal Academic/Admin Structure)
  The internal hierarchy WITHIN one entity.
  Faculty → Department → Programme → Admin Unit → Committee
  An OrgUnit belongs to exactly ONE InstitutionEntity. Never spans entities.
  Faculty staff manage these within their entity.

## Visual Model
```
Institution: University of Lagos
│
├── InstitutionEntity: MAIN_CAMPUS (INTERNAL, BILLED_TO_PARENT)
│   ├── OrgUnit: Faculty of Engineering (FACULTY)
│   │   ├── OrgUnit: Dept. of Computer Science (DEPARTMENT)
│   │   │   └── OrgUnit: BSc Computer Science (PROGRAMME)
│   │   └── OrgUnit: Dept. of Electrical Engineering (DEPARTMENT)
│   ├── OrgUnit: Registry (ADMIN_UNIT)
│   └── OrgUnit: Finance Office (ADMIN_UNIT)
│
├── InstitutionEntity: EXTRAMURAL (INTERNAL, BILLED_TO_PARENT)
│   ├── OrgUnit: Evening Division (FACULTY)
│   └── OrgUnit: Weekend Division (FACULTY)
│
├── InstitutionEntity: SCHOOL_OF_MEDICINE (SCHOOL, INTERNAL, BILLED_TO_PARENT)
│   ├── OrgUnit: Dept. of Medicine (DEPARTMENT)
│   └── OrgUnit: Dept. of Pharmacy (DEPARTMENT)
│
├── InstitutionEntity: KINGS_COLLEGE (CONSTITUENT_COLLEGE, PARTIAL, BILLED_TO_PARENT)
│   └── OrgUnit: Sciences (FACULTY)
│
└── InstitutionEntity: COVENANT_UNIV (AFFILIATE, EXTERNAL, BILLED_INDEPENDENTLY)
    └── (API access only — student verification)
```

# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 6 — BILLING MODEL
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

## 6.1 The One Billing Rule

  BILLABLE   = student.enrollmentStatus == 'ACTIVE'
  NOT BILLABLE = any other status

  This is the COMPLETE billing rule. No exceptions.
  No platform-access backstop. No balance backstop.
  Status is the sole contract between UniCore and the institution.

## 6.2 Why This Is Fraud-Proof

  If an institution marks a student INACTIVE to avoid billing:
    → Student is IMMEDIATELY and SYNCHRONOUSLY logged out
    → Institution CANNOT post ANY records for that student
      (enforced at API middleware level — StudentRecordPostingGuard)
    → No grades, no attendance, no enrollments, no LMS activity,
      no financial charges, no documents issued for that student
    → A gap appears in the student's academic record
    → That gap HARMS the institution (accreditation, transcripts,
      regulatory compliance audits) — NOT UniCore
    → The institution is self-punishing for attempting to game billing

  If the institution later wants to post records for the inactive period:
    → Must submit a BackfillRequest through workflow
    → Must explicitly acknowledge the retroactive billing consequence
    → The FULL inactive period is billed retroactively upon approval
    → Records are permanently marked: isBackfilled: true

  The institution cannot have it both ways:
    Either inactive (no records, no bill) OR active (records, billed).

## 6.3 Student Status Definitions

  ACTIVE
    Billable. Student has full platform access.
    Institution has full read/write access to all student records.

  INACTIVE  (all non-active states use this status)
    NOT billable. Student is IMMEDIATELY locked out (synchronous).
    Student CANNOT log in to any part of the platform.
    Institution can VIEW existing profile and records ONLY.
    Institution CANNOT post any new records of any type.
    Sub-reasons (informational only — do NOT change billing logic):
      DEFERRED            Approved leave of absence (medical, maternity, etc.)
      RUSTICATED          Temporary academic suspension
      EXPELLED            Disciplinary removal
      TRANSFERRED_OUT     Student moved to another institution entirely
      GRADUATED           Completed their programme
      WITHDRAWN           Student's own request to leave
      SUSPENDED_PENDING   Pending disciplinary decision

  PERMANENTLY_DELETED
    Institution's explicit, irreversible decision.
    Student record anonymised. Auth user hard-deleted.
    Billing history retained for UniCore audit.
    Academic records de-identified but retained for statistics.

## 6.4 Student Status Transitions

  ADMITTED      → ACTIVE           (admission accepted, account created)
  ACTIVE        → INACTIVE         (any sub-reason — requires Registrar)
  INACTIVE      → ACTIVE           (reactivation — requires workflow approval)
  INACTIVE      → INACTIVE         (sub-reason change — e.g., SUSPENDED_PENDING → EXPELLED)
  INACTIVE      → PERMANENTLY_DELETED (requires workflow: Registrar + Deputy VC + Finance)
  ACTIVE        → PERMANENTLY_DELETED  FORBIDDEN — must go through INACTIVE first

## 6.5 Records Integrity Rule

  No record of any kind may be posted for a student during any period
  when that student held INACTIVE status.

  "Records" includes ALL of:
    Academic:   section enrollment, grade entry, attendance marking,
                timetable assignment, assessment submissions
    Financial:  fee charges, scholarship awards, payment plan creation
                (EXCEPTION: receiving payments — clears pre-existing debt)
    LMS:        course access, lesson completion, quiz attempts,
                discussion posts, assignment submissions
    Admin:      document issuance, disciplinary records, clearance updates,
                hostel assignment, medical records posting

  ENFORCEMENT: NestJS middleware — StudentRecordPostingGuard
  This is infrastructure-level enforcement, NOT application convention.
  The guard applies BEFORE every controller that writes student-associated data.

## 6.6 Reactivation and Retroactive Billing

  REACTIVATION (INACTIVE → ACTIVE):
    Requires: written justification + Registrar authority + workflow approval
    On workflow approval:
      Student receives immediate full platform access
      Institution billed from reactivation date forward (normal billing)

  BACKFILL REQUEST (posting records for an inactive period):
    Used when institution needs academic records for a period when the
    student was officially INACTIVE but academically active (e.g. student
    was on approved deferment and still took supervised exams).

    Process:
      1. Institution submits BackfillRequest (fromDate, toDate, justification)
      2. System shows estimated retroactive fee BEFORE submission
      3. Institution must explicitly acknowledge billing consequence
      4. WorkflowEngine: HoD → Dean → Registrar → Finance
      5. On full approval:
         a. BackfillWindow created { studentId, fromDate, toDate }
         b. StudentRecordPostingGuard allows writes within this window
         c. All records posted in window: isBackfilled: true (permanent)
         d. Retroactive invoice generated immediately
      6. BackfillWindow auto-expires at toDate

    Full inactive period is billed — no cherry-picking of individual days.

## 6.7 Permanent Deletion

  Preconditions (ALL must be true before workflow can start):
    1. enrollmentStatus is NOT ACTIVE
    2. All outstanding financial balances = 0
    3. No active workflow instances involving the student
    4. Regulatory retention period passed (default: 7 years post-graduation)

  Workflow: Registrar (typed confirmation: studentNumber) →
            Deputy VC (approve) → Finance (confirm $0 balance) →
            System executes

  On execution:
    - Student name, email, phone, photo → replaced with anonymised IDs
    - studentNumber retained for statistical integrity
    - All academic records retained but de-identified
    - Billing history retained for UniCore financial audit
    - Auth user record: HARD DELETED (irreversible)
    - Institution sees anonymised statistical record only

## 6.8 Daily Billing Snapshot

  DailySnapshotJob runs at 02:00 UTC daily.
  For each ACTIVE institution, for each ACTIVE entity:

    billableCount = SELECT COUNT(*) FROM students
                    WHERE institutionId = X
                    AND entityId = Y
                    AND enrollmentStatus = 'ACTIVE'
                    AND deletedAt IS NULL

    Stored in DailyBillableSnapshot — immutable after creation.
    Only UniCore super admin can amend with mandatory reason + audit log.

  Monthly invoice computation:
    MONTHLY_WATERMARK:    MAX(peak daily count, average daily count)
    ANNUAL_PEAK:          highest single-day count in the academic year
    SEMESTER_HEADCOUNT:   count on Semester.censusDate

## 6.9 Billing Models

  MONTHLY_WATERMARK (recommended for most institutions):
    Bill monthly. Count = MAX(peakDayCount, avgDayCount) for the month.
    The MAX of both prevents: "deactivate before billing day" trick
    AND "deactivate for billing day only" trick simultaneously.

  ANNUAL_PEAK (stable enrolment, traditional universities):
    Bill once per year. Count = highest single-day count in academic year.
    Minimum commitment: contracted floor count (no refund if below).

  SEMESTER_HEADCOUNT (academic-calendar aligned):
    Bill per semester. Count = billable students on Semester.censusDate.
    Backstop: if student accessed platform after census date in the semester,
    they are counted for that full semester regardless.

# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 7 — UNIVERSITY HIERARCHY & AUTHORITY MODEL
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

## 7.1 Position Levels (Authority Ranking)

  Level 1:  VC / President / Rector / Principal (entity head)
  Level 2:  Deputy VC / Provost / Deputy Principal
  Level 2:  Registrar (parallel admin authority — equal to Deputy VC)
  Level 3:  Deans / Directors (Finance Dir., Library Dir., IT Dir.,
            Student Affairs Dir., HR Dir., Alumni Dir., Sports Dir.,
            Admissions Dir., Research Dir.)
  Level 4:  HoD / Bursar / Unit Head / Deputy Bursar
  Level 5:  Programme Coordinator / Section Head / Sub-unit Head
  Level 6:  Senior Lecturer / Senior Staff
  Level 7:  Lecturer / Staff / Adjunct / Tutor

## 7.2 Entity Scope Types

  INSTITUTION   All entities within the institution (VC, Registrar, Deputy VC)
  ENTITY        One InstitutionEntity (Principal, Entity Registrar)
  FACULTY       One Faculty OrgUnit within an entity
  DEPARTMENT    One Department OrgUnit within a faculty
  PROGRAMME     One Programme OrgUnit within a department
  UNIT          One Admin Unit OrgUnit
  SECTION       Own assigned courses and sections only
  PERSONAL      Own data only (students, staff self-service)

## 7.3 JWT Entity Scope

  entityScope: 'ALL'    → VC, Deputy VC, Registrar, institution Directors
                           Middleware injects: where { institutionId }
                           Sees data across ALL entities

  entityScope: 'ENTITY' → All other positions (Principal, Dean, HoD, etc.)
                           Middleware injects: where { institutionId, entityId }
                           Sees data within their entity ONLY

## 7.4 Standard Approval Chains (all via WorkflowDefinition records)

  GRADE_ENTRY:
    Lecturer enters → HoD reviews → Dean approves → Entity Registrar publishes

  GRADE_OVERRIDE:
    Student requests → Lecturer comments → HoD reviews →
    Dean approves → Entity Registrar executes

  GRADUATION_CLEARANCE:
    Programme Coord (credits) → HoD (certify) → Dean (endorse) →
    Entity Registrar (confirm) → Finance (clear balance) →
    Library (clear) → VC/Institution Registrar (approve)

  STUDENT_SUSPENSION (disciplinary):
    HoD (initiate) → Dean of Students (review) →
    Entity Head (approve) → Deputy VC → VC (ratify) →
    Institution Registrar (execute)

  STUDENT_REACTIVATION:
    HoD (recommend) → Dean (endorse) →
    Entity Registrar (confirm + set date) → System executes

  BACKFILL_REQUEST:
    HoD (review academic justification) → Dean (approve) →
    Entity Registrar (final approval) → Finance (retroactive invoice) →
    System creates BackfillWindow

  STUDENT_PERMANENT_DELETION:
    Registrar (initiate + typed confirmation) →
    Deputy VC (approve) → Finance (confirm $0 balance) →
    System anonymises + hard-deletes auth user

  COURSE_CREATION:
    Lecturer (propose) → HoD (approve) → Dean (endorse) →
    Academic Board (ratify) → Entity Registrar (catalog)

  BUDGET_REQUEST:
    Unit Head (submit) → Entity Director (review) →
    Entity Finance (assess) → Institution Finance Director (approve) →
    Deputy VC (sign off if above threshold)

  SCHOLARSHIP_AWARD:
    Scholarships Committee (score) → Finance Director (validate funds) →
    Deputy VC (approve) → Institution Registrar (notify)

  LEAVE_REQUEST:
    Staff (apply) → Line Manager (approve) → HoD (endorse) →
    HR Director (note)

  STUDENT_TRANSFER (between entities):
    Source Entity Registrar → Dest Entity Registrar →
    Institution Registrar (log) → System updates entityId
    (Student stays ACTIVE throughout — no billing gap)

  ENTITY_CREATION:
    Institution Admin initiates → System auto-provisions entity

  AFFILIATE_LINK:
    Entity Admin (request) → Institution VC/Registrar (approve) →
    System creates AffiliateLink + API key

# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 8 — DATA SCOPING RULES (THE LAW)
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

## 8.1 JWT Payload Structure

  interface UniCoreJwtPayload {
    sub:               string    // userId
    email:             string
    institutionId:     string    // always present — tenant boundary
    entityId:          string    // which entity they belong to
    entityScope:       'ALL' | 'ENTITY'
    positionCode:      string    // "VC"|"PRINCIPAL"|"DEAN"|"HOD"|"REG"
    positionLevel:     number    // 1–7
    positionScope:     string    // INSTITUTION|ENTITY|FACULTY|DEPT|PERSONAL
    orgUnitId:         string    // OrgUnit they lead/belong to
    permissionBundles: string[]  // capability groups
    permissions:       string[]  // expanded individual permissions
    isSuperAdmin:      boolean
  }

## 8.2 PrismaTenantMiddleware Injection Rules

  entityScope 'ALL'    → inject where: { institutionId, deletedAt: null }
  entityScope 'ENTITY' → inject where: { institutionId, entityId, deletedAt: null }
  Super admin bypass   → no automatic injection (explicit bypass flag)

  CRITICAL: Services NEVER add institutionId or entityId manually.
  The middleware handles it for every query automatically.
  Manual additions create maintenance risk and scope inconsistencies.

## 8.3 Who Sees What

  Platform Super Admin    → ANY institution, ANY entity, ALL data
  Institution VC/Registrar → ALL entities within their institution
  Entity Principal/Director → ONLY their entity's data
  Dean / Director (entity)  → ONLY their faculty/unit within their entity
  HoD                       → ONLY their department within their entity
  Lecturer / Staff          → ONLY their assigned sections/courses
  Student                   → ONLY their own personal data
  Affiliate (EXTERNAL)      → API-scoped only (verify-student, verify-transcript)

# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 9 — UNIVERSAL LAWS (NEVER VIOLATE)
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

These laws apply to every file generated in this project.
A violation is a bug or a security incident, not a style choice.

LAW 1 — DUAL SCOPE ISOLATION [P0 — SECURITY]
  Every institution-scoped model MUST have BOTH fields:
    institutionId  String   ← cross-tenant wall
    entityId       String   ← cross-entity wall
  Middleware injects both automatically. No service adds them manually.
  Missing institutionId on a query = P0 cross-tenant breach.
  Missing entityId (for ENTITY-scope actor) = P1 cross-entity breach.

LAW 2 — ENTITY SCOPE GUARD [P0 — SECURITY]
  @UseGuards(EntityScopeGuard) on EVERY controller endpoint that
  reads or writes entity-scoped data. The guard validates:
    a) Resource's institutionId matches actor's institutionId
    b) Resource's entityId matches actor's entityId
       (UNLESS actor has entityScope: 'ALL')
  No exception without explicit justification and @SuperAdminOnly.

LAW 3 — STUDENT RECORD POSTING GUARD [P0 — BILLING INTEGRITY]
  @UseGuards(StudentRecordPostingGuard) on EVERY endpoint that writes
  any record associated with a student.
  Guard logic:
    If student.enrollmentStatus == 'ACTIVE' → allow
    If approved BackfillWindow covers this date → allow, mark isBackfilled: true
    Otherwise → throw 403 STUDENT_INACTIVE
  No bypass except @BypassRecordGuard() which requires @SuperAdminOnly().

LAW 4 — INSTANT LOGOUT ON INACTIVATION [SYNCHRONOUS]
  When student status changes to INACTIVE (any sub-reason):
  Within the SAME database transaction, before response is returned:
    1. DEL refresh:{institutionId}:*:{userId}:*  (flush refresh tokens)
    2. GET all JTIs for this user, SET token_blocked:{jti} 1 EX {ttl}
    3. Emit 'session.terminated' to student's WebSocket room
  This is NOT a background job. It is synchronous and immediate.
  Student is unreachable on the platform the moment status changes.

LAW 5 — READ-ONLY FOR INACTIVE STUDENTS
  API: StudentRecordPostingGuard blocks all write operations
  UI:  All form inputs disabled, all action buttons hidden
       INACTIVE banner prominently displayed on student profile
  Permitted for institution on inactive student:
    View existing profile and all historical records
    Download existing documents
    Initiate reactivation workflow
    Submit backfill request
    Initiate permanent deletion workflow (if preconditions met)

LAW 6 — STATUS CHANGES ONLY VIA StatusChangeService
  Student.enrollmentStatus is NEVER written directly anywhere.
  The ONLY code that writes it is StatusChangeService.changeStatus().
  Any other path is a bug. Period.

LAW 7 — STATUS CHANGE LOG IS IMMUTABLE
  StatusChangeLog records: no updatedAt, no deletedAt, no UPDATE, no DELETE.
  Every status change creates a NEW record. Never amends an existing one.
  Violations are security incidents, not bugs.

LAW 8 — BACKFILLED RECORDS FLAGGED PERMANENTLY
  Every record posted via an approved BackfillWindow must have:
    isBackfilled: true  (set by guard from request.backfillContext)
    backfillRequestId: string  (reference to the approval)
  These flags never change. Visible in all views. Cannot be removed.

LAW 9 — SNAPSHOT IMMUTABILITY AFTER INVOICE LOCK
  DailyBillableSnapshot records are write-once by BillingSnapshotService.
  After the monthly invoice is generated, they are locked for billing.
  Only UniCore super admin can amend locked snapshots.
  Amendment requires mandatory written reason + AuditLog entry.
  Institution users have READ-ONLY access to snapshots. Never write.

LAW 10 — HIERARCHICAL AUTHORITY ON EVERY WRITE
  Every write operation checks position level + scope + permission bundle.
  @RequirePosition() @RequirePermission() @RequireScope() always applied.
  Never hardcode role names. Always use the Position system.
  A Dean cannot act on another Faculty's data.
  An HoD cannot act on another Department's data.

LAW 11 — WORKFLOW ENFORCEMENT
  All multi-step approvals go through WorkflowEngine only.
  No service implements its own approval logic.
  Reactivation, backfill, permanent deletion, grade overrides,
  graduation clearance — all via WorkflowDefinition records.

LAW 12 — AUDIT EVERY MUTATION
  AuditLogService.log({
    institutionId, entityId,
    actorId, actorPosition,
    action, entity, entityId_record,
    oldValues, newValues,
    ipAddress, userAgent,
    billingImplication?   (GAIN | LOSS | RETROACTIVE_GAIN | NONE)
  })
  Status changes ALWAYS include billingImplication in audit log.
  Cross-entity operations: isCrossEntity: true flag.

LAW 13 — SOFT DELETE EVERYWHERE
  No prisma.*.delete() calls anywhere in service code.
  Standard deletion: set deletedAt = new Date()
  Permanent deletion (student): anonymise fields + hard-delete Auth user only.

LAW 14 — TYPED, NEVER ANY
  TypeScript strict mode: ON.
  No `any`. No `as any`. No `!.` non-null assertions.
  Use `unknown` + type guards where type is genuinely uncertain.
  Explicit return types on all service methods and API handlers.

LAW 15 — CURSOR-BASED PAGINATION ON ALL LIST ENDPOINTS
  Request:  { cursor?: string, limit: number, direction?: 'asc'|'desc' }
  Response: { data: T[], nextCursor: string | null, total: number }
  Never use offset pagination in production list endpoints.

LAW 16 — STANDARDISED ERROR FORMAT
  { statusCode, errorCode, message, details?, timestamp, path, traceId }
  errorCode namespaced: "STUDENT_001", "BILLING_003", "AUTH_007"
  All error codes documented in packages/types/src/errors.ts

LAW 17 — NO CROSS-APP IMPORTS
  apps/api ↔ apps/web ↔ apps/admin: zero direct imports.
  Cross-app sharing ONLY through packages/*.
  NestJS code never enters apps/web or apps/admin.
  Next.js code never enters apps/api.

LAW 18 — ENTITY PROVISIONING ON CREATE
  Creating an InstitutionEntity MUST trigger full provisioning:
    a) Default OrgUnit tree (based on entity type template)
    b) Head position created (Principal/Director/Provost)
    c) WorkflowDefinitions copied from institution template
    d) Entity-specific Subscription (if BILLED_INDEPENDENTLY)
    e) Entity settings initialised from type defaults
    f) 'entity.provisioned' event emitted
  Never create a bare entity without full provisioning.

LAW 19 — CONSOLIDATED REPORTING ALWAYS AVAILABLE
  Institution-wide users (entityScope: ALL) always see data across
  ALL entities aggregated. Never return partial data to ALL-scope actors.
  Every report must include an entity breakdown column or row.
  Consolidated totals must always equal the sum of entity totals.

LAW 20 — OPENAPI DOCS ON EVERY ENDPOINT
  @ApiTags, @ApiOperation, @ApiResponse on every controller method.
  All DTOs decorated with @ApiProperty.
  No undocumented endpoints in production code.

