# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 11 — CODING STANDARDS
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

## NestJS Standards
- One responsibility per service method — no god methods
- Controllers are THIN: validate input → call service → return response
- Services contain ALL business logic
- Repositories contain ALL Prisma queries
- Middleware injects scope — services NEVER add institutionId/entityId manually
- Student.enrollmentStatus ONLY written by StatusChangeService.changeStatus()
- Instant logout: synchronous within status change transaction
- StudentRecordPostingGuard applied globally on all student-write endpoints
- Constructor injection always — never property injection
- No circular module imports — explicit module registration
- ConfigService for ALL env vars — never process.env directly
- Async/await always — no raw Promise chains
- BullMQ jobs: attempts: 3, backoff: exponential, removeOnComplete: false

## Next.js Standards
- Server Components by default — Client Components only for interactivity
- 'use client' at the top of Client Components
- Server Components fetch via direct API calls (no useEffect for initial data)
- Client-side mutations via TanStack Query useMutation
- useEntityContext() available in all institution-scoped pages
- useStudentStatus(studentId) available for all student-related forms
- INACTIVE student pages: full read-only mode (inputs disabled + banner)
- loading.tsx + Suspense + Skeleton for loading states
- error.tsx + ErrorBoundary for error states
- TanStack Query: staleTime + cacheTime configured per query type

## TypeScript Standards
- Strict mode ON — tsconfig: { "strict": true }
- Interfaces for object shapes, types for unions and primitives
- Enums must match Prisma enums exactly
- No non-null assertions (!.) — use optional chaining (?.)
- Explicit return types on ALL service methods and API handlers
- Generic types for reusable utilities

## Naming Conventions
- Files:        kebab-case   (status-change.service.ts)
- Classes:      PascalCase   (StatusChangeService)
- Interfaces:   I prefix     (IStatusChangeDto, IBillableCount)
- Enums:        PascalCase   (EnrollmentStatus, InactiveReason)
- DB tables:    snake_case via @@map  (status_change_logs)
- DB columns:   camelCase in Prisma, snake_case in DB via @map
- API routes:   kebab-case   (/institution-entities, /billing/snapshots)
- React comps:  PascalCase   (InactiveBanner.tsx, EntitySwitcher.tsx)
- Hooks:        use prefix   (useStudentStatus.ts, useEntityContext.ts)
- Stores:       Store suffix (entityStore.ts, sidebarStore.ts)
- Query keys:   string[]     (['students', entityId, studentId, 'status'])

# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 12 — SECURITY REQUIREMENTS
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

1.  Never log passwords, tokens, MFA secrets, or payment card data
2.  Student instant logout: synchronous within status change transaction
3.  JWT blocklist: active tokens invalidated immediately on inactivation
4.  StudentRecordPostingGuard: no bypass without @SuperAdminOnly
5.  DailyBillableSnapshot: READ only for institution users — never WRITE
6.  StatusChangeLog: IMMUTABLE — no UPDATE or DELETE ever
7.  BackfillRequest: billing acknowledgment enforced before workflow starts
8.  Permanent deletion: typed confirmation + full workflow + irreversible
9.  Cross-entity access: CRITICAL security event → AuditLog + alert
10. EXTERNAL affiliate API: STUDENT_VERIFY and TRANSCRIPT_VERIFY only
    Returns only: enrolled: boolean, programme: string (no PII)
11. Presigned S3 URLs: max 1 hour expiry
12. File uploads: magic byte MIME type validation (not extension)
13. Auth rate limiting: 5 attempts per 15 minutes on auth endpoints
14. Refresh token rotation: old token invalidated on every use
15. CORS: whitelist institution domains + entity custom domains only
16. Helmet.js: CSP, HSTS, X-Frame-Options, X-Content-Type-Options
17. Entity switcher: always issues fresh JWT — never mutates existing token
18. Entity deletion: BLOCKED if entity has ACTIVE students (hard block)
19. Webhook signatures: ALWAYS verified before processing payloads
20. Sensitive field encryption: salary, payment gateway configs, MFA secrets,
    SSO configs → AES-256-GCM with per-institution derived keys

# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 13 — TESTING REQUIREMENTS
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Coverage target: 80% minimum on all modules.

## Critical Tests (must pass before ANY deployment)

BILLING INTEGRITY:
  [ ] ACTIVE student → counted in DailyBillableSnapshot
  [ ] INACTIVE student (any sub-reason) → NOT counted
  [ ] Status → INACTIVE → student session terminated synchronously
  [ ] INACTIVE student: POST /grades → 403 STUDENT_INACTIVE
  [ ] INACTIVE student: POST /attendance → 403 STUDENT_INACTIVE
  [ ] INACTIVE student: POST /enrollments → 403 STUDENT_INACTIVE
  [ ] INACTIVE student: POST /lms/submissions → 403 STUDENT_INACTIVE
  [ ] INACTIVE student: GET /students/:id → 200 (read allowed)
  [ ] Approved BackfillWindow → POST /grades allowed for approved period
  [ ] Backfill records → isBackfilled: true on all records
  [ ] Backfill approval → retroactive invoice generated
  [ ] Backfill records outside approved window → 403
  [ ] Permanent deletion → auth user deleted → student cannot log in
  [ ] Permanent deletion → academic records anonymised + retained
  [ ] Student transfer → status stays ACTIVE → snapshot unchanged
  [ ] StatusChangeLog → no UPDATE query ever executed
  [ ] DailyBillableSnapshot → no institution user can write/update it

ENTITY ISOLATION:
  [ ] Entity A user: GET /students → only Entity A students returned
  [ ] Entity A user: GET /students/{Entity B student id} → 403 or 404
  [ ] Institution VC (entityScope: ALL): GET /students → all entities returned
  [ ] Entity switcher: cannot switch to a different institution's entity

## Standard Tests Per Module
  Unit tests:        every service method (mocked dependencies)
  Integration tests: every controller endpoint (Supertest + Testcontainers)
  DB tests:          Testcontainers (real PostgreSQL, not SQLite mock)

# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 14 — DEFINITION OF DONE
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

A feature is ONLY done when ALL of the following are complete:

Schema & Data:
  [ ] Prisma schema updated with institutionId + entityId on all scoped models
  [ ] Migration file generated and tested
  [ ] Seed data updated if needed

Backend:
  [ ] Service methods complete with correct business logic
  [ ] Status changes ONLY via StatusChangeService
  [ ] StudentRecordPostingGuard applied on all student-write endpoints
  [ ] EntityScopeGuard on all entity-scoped endpoints
  [ ] PositionGuard + PermissionGuard applied
  [ ] WorkflowEngine integration (if approval needed)
  [ ] AuditLog call on every mutation (with entityId + billingImplication)
  [ ] DTOs with class-validator on all controller methods
  [ ] OpenAPI decorators (@ApiTags, @ApiOperation, @ApiResponse)

Testing:
  [ ] Unit tests for all service methods (80%+ coverage)
  [ ] Integration tests for all controller endpoints
  [ ] Entity isolation test passing
  [ ] Billing integrity tests passing (if student-related feature)
  [ ] StatusChangeLog immutability verified (if status-related)

Frontend:
  [ ] Page component complete with loading + error + empty states
  [ ] TanStack Query hook with correct cache keys
  [ ] Zod form schema matching backend DTO
  [ ] Entity context visible in UI (entity badge on records)
  [ ] INACTIVE student: banner shown + all inputs disabled
  [ ] Status timeline on student profile (if student feature)
  [ ] Entity switcher works (if multi-entity user)

Quality:
  [ ] No TypeScript errors (strict mode)
  [ ] No ESLint errors
  [ ] Notification triggered on all user-facing actions
  [ ] Consolidated view works for institution-wide users
  [ ] Mobile responsive (if user-facing page)
